&lt;p>Path of the &lt;code>authorized_keys&lt;/code> file which contains the SSH keys that can be used for logging into the remote hosts.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>SSH Authentication</title><link>https://ssham.pacoorozco.info/about/ssh-authentication/</link><pubDate>Tue, 10 May 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://ssham.pacoorozco.info/about/ssh-authentication/</guid><description>&lt;p>SSH authentication is broadly categorized into two types: &lt;em>password-based&lt;/em> and &lt;em>public key authentication&lt;/em>.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="flex align-center gdoc-page__anchorwrap">
 &lt;h2 id="1-password-based-authentication"
 >
 1. Password-based authentication
 &lt;/h2>
 &lt;a data-clipboard-text="https://ssham.pacoorozco.info/about/ssh-authentication/#1-password-based-authentication" class="gdoc-page__anchor clip flex align-center" title="Anchor to: 1. Password-based authentication" aria-label="Anchor to: 1. Password-based authentication" href="#1-password-based-authentication">
 &lt;svg class="gdoc-icon gdoc_link">&lt;use xlink:href="#gdoc_link">&lt;/use>&lt;/svg>
 &lt;/a>
&lt;/div>
&lt;p>In &lt;em>password-based authentication&lt;/em>, the client sends an authentication request to the server which includes the encrypted username and password for the remote server. Upon receipt, the server decrypts the request and validates the credentials in plain text. Once verified, the client is notified of the authentication outcome.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Authorization</title><link>https://ssham.pacoorozco.info/using-ssham/auth/</link><pubDate>Tue, 10 May 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://ssham.pacoorozco.info/using-ssham/auth/</guid><description>&lt;p>There are 4 roles that you can assign to users. Each role provides different &lt;a
